<speech id="uk.org.publicwhip/wms/2006-10-11a.53.5" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/lord/100067" speakername="Lord Brabazon of Tara" colon=":" colnum="53"  url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/ld199900/ldhansrd/pdvn/lds06/text/61011-wms0001.htm#spnew_255">
	<p pid="a.53.5/1">The resolution of the House of <phrase class="date" code="1994-07-20">20 July 1994</phrase> provided for the limits of the subsistence and office cost allowances to be uprated annually on <phrase class="date" code="2006-08-01">1 August</phrase> in line with the increase in the retail prices index over the previous 12 months to July.</p>
	<p pid="a.53.5/2">Accordingly, the limits within which Lords may be reimbursed expenses incurred were increased with effect from <phrase class="date" code="2006-08-01">1 August 2006</phrase>. The new limits are now as follows (the limits previously applicable are shown in brackets).</p>
	<table>
		<tbody>
			<tr pid="a.53.5/5"> <td>Overnight subsistence</td> <td>&pound;159.50</td> <td>(&pound;154.50)</td> </tr>
			<tr pid="a.53.5/6"> <td>Day subsistence</td> <td>&pound;79.50</td> <td>(&pound;77)</td> </tr>
			<tr pid="a.53.5/7"> <td>Office costs</td> <td>&pound;69.00</td> <td>(&pound;67)</td> </tr>
			<tr pid="a.53.5/8"> <td>Office costs for non-sitting periods</td> <td>&pound;2,760.00</td> <td>(&pound;2,680)</td> </tr>
			<tr pid="a.53.5/9"> <td></td> <td>40 days @ &pound;69</td> <td>(&pound;67)</td> </tr>
		</tbody>
	</table>
</speech>
